  "text": "We could speculate that route flexibility in longrange migration allows responses to critical factors like wind conditions, availability of suitable stopover sites and physical condition that change between years and regions. Such flexibility in route choice must be of much less potential adaptive value for movements over short distances and durations, e.g. by homing pigeons. In agreement with this idea is the suggestion that short-term environmental variability, rather than distance minimization and route fidelity, shapes the routes of the dark-bellied brent geese Branta bernicla bernicla [CITATION_1] .",
